messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 2/16/03 12:16:58 AM, katguts@... writes:

<< Good things NEVER happen in corn in
movies!!!" :) >>

Wasn't Field of Dreams an okay corn movie?
No, maybe not...

Lord of the Rings! No, scared the crap out of hobbits.

<<And I assured my husband that we would never, as long as I
am breathing, ever have corn fields. They're just creepy!!! Even without
aliens in them!!!>>

But corn is good. <g>

We had corn fields sometimes when I was a kid Never over 1/4 an acre, but it
can be creepy even in a small cornfield, when it's getting dry and makes
scary bug-noises everywhere if the wind moves. And sometimes corn even has
scary bugs! (Worms, not bugs, but still...)

Sandra

messages.messageBody:
That movie scared the crap out of me!!! The whole time I kept saying "don't
go in the corn!!! Burn the corn down!!! Good things NEVER happen in corn in
movies!!!" :) And I assured my husband that we would never, as long as I
am breathing, ever have corn fields. They're just creepy!!! Even without
aliens in them!!!
I liked that movie though. Loved Mel. MMmmmmm :)

Katie
